<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2">
<Document>
  <name>Kyoto Night Walk · Golden Path</name>
  <description><![CDATA[5 stops × A/B · 🥞 okonomiyaki · 🍋 chuhai · 🍶 sake · 🍺 craft beer · all walk-in]]></description>

  <Style id="locked"><IconStyle><scale>1.3</scale><Icon><href>https://maps.google.com/mapfiles/kml/paddle/ylw-stars.png</href></Icon></IconStyle></Style>
  <Style id="major"><IconStyle><scale>1.1</scale><Icon><href>https://maps.google.com/mapfiles/kml/paddle/red-circle.png</href></Icon></IconStyle></Style>
  <Style id="bonus"><IconStyle><scale>0.9</scale><Icon><href>https://maps.google.com/mapfiles/kml/paddle/blu-blank.png</href></Icon></IconStyle></Style>
  <Style id="station"><IconStyle><scale>0.9</scale><Icon><href>https://maps.google.com/mapfiles/kml/shapes/rail.png</href></Icon></IconStyle></Style>

  <Folder>
    <name>LOCKED — confirmed bookings / hard anchors</name>
    <Placemark>
      <name>Ritz-Carlton Kyoto — start &amp; end</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Start ~17:30 · loop back via Gion by ~midnight</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Home base. The night-walk is a loop: walk south down Kiyamachi → cross to Pontocho/Shinkyogoku → cross Shijo-Ohashi to Gion → walk back via Kamogawa.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> All 5 golden-path stops walkable. Backup picks (bonus pins) scattered along the same loop.<br><br>Address: Kamogawa Nijo-Ohashi Hotori, Nakagyo-ku]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#locked</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.77078,35.01428,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
  </Folder>

  <Folder>
    <name>MAJOR — the planned spine</name>
    <Placemark>
      <name>🍶 Tachinomi Origami (立ち呑み処 origami)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 1 PRIMARY · 17:30 · Sun-Thu 17:00-01:00 · open year-round</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> 14-seat standing counter, 50+ jizake / 100+ shochu/chuhai/highball. Fried small plates, sashimi.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Tabelog 4.48 (very high). The opener — deep sake list, Japanese-majority, near Ritz. Walk-in primary.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区紙屋町363 オーシャンビル 1F<br><br><b>↪ ~10 min south from Ritz on Kiyamachi</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7696,35.0071,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍋 Suiba bal 河原町BAL北店 (Suiba Bal Kita)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 1 SECONDARY · 12:00-15:00 + 17:00-03:00 · closed Tue</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Standing chuhai bar with extended late-night hours. Chuhai, lemon sour, kushi, oden.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Backup if Origami is packed. Open till 03:00 — also works as the LAST stop of the night if needed.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区河原町通三条下ル北車屋町261-1 1F<br><br><b>↪ ~10 min from Ritz (Kawaramachi-Sanjo)</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76828,35.00833,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍋 たつみ (Tatsumi) — Kyoto Three Great Sakaba</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 2 PRIMARY · ⚠ LO 20:50 · CLOSED Thursday · go by 19:30</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Voted 'Kyoto Three Great Sakaba' by Japanese locals magazine potel.jp. Hi-Riki Lemon chuhai + highball + sake. Standing or back tatami.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> THE chuhai destination of the night. ⚠ Must hit by 19:30 to be safe — LO 20:50 means kitchen stops then.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区裏寺町通四条上ル中之町572<br><br><b>↪ ~14 min from Ritz · 2 min from Hankyu Kawaramachi station</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76859,35.00404,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍋 すいば 四条河原町 (Suiba Shijo Kawaramachi)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 2 SECONDARY · Mon-Fri 16:00-24:00 · LO 23:30 · closed Mon + 1st Tue</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Standing chuhai bar, casual. Lemon sour, takowasa, agedashi tofu, kushikatsu.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Tatsumi backup. Open till 24:00 = much more forgiving timing.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区中之町569-2<br><br><b>↪ ~14 min from Ritz, near Tatsumi</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76876,35.00385,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🥞🍋 鉄板 みつ喜 (Teppan Mitsuki) — POSCHO OKONOMIYAKI</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 3 PRIMARY DINNER · Tue-Sun 18:00-01:00 LO 24:00 · CLOSED Mon</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Pontocho okonomiyaki + teppan. Water-free signature style (denser batter). Treated as a drinking-spot first, food second. Fresh chuhai/lemon sours.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Pontocho alley okonomiyaki, à la carte, walk-in friendly, open late. Tabelog Magazine Japanese article featured as the locals-frequented teppan. ⭐ One of three top-tier okonomiyaki on the map.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区木屋町四条上ル下樵木町192<br><br><b>↪ ~15 min from Ritz, Pontocho alley near Shijo</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.77068,35.00339,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🥞🍋 祇園たんと (Gion Tanto) — SHIRAKAWA OKONOMIYAKI</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 3 SECONDARY DINNER · Wed 16:30-21:30 LO 21:30 · CLOSED Thursday</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Kyoto-style fluffy okonomiyaki + teppan + chuhai. Small neighborhood counter on Shirakawa Canal near Tatsumi Bridge.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Gion-side okonomiyaki, no reservations, à la carte. ⚠ Closes 21:30 — earlier dinner if doing Tanto. Cross Shijo-Ohashi to reach it.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区清本町372<br><br><b>↪ ~12 min from Ritz south along Kamogawa, cross Shijo-Ohashi</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7745,35.00455,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍺 GION TACHINOMI 山根子 (Yamaneko)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 4 PRIMARY · Daily 11:00-24:00 · cash-on per drink</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Tachinomi inside 150-year-old machiya. 8 Kyoto craft beers on tap + sake refrigerator self-serve. Maizuru dried fish, hotaru-ika (firefly squid).<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> The Gion machiya pick. Craft beer + sake program in a preserved Edo-era building. Cash-on-per-drink = no tab, pure walk-in.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区祇園町北側321-1<br><br><b>↪ ~13 min from Ritz · 5 min from Gion-Shijo station</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.77735,35.00375,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>山口大亭 東店 (Yamaguchi Daitei Higashi) — 50yr izakaya</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 4 SECONDARY · Mon-Thu/Sat 17:00-22:00 LO 21:30 · CLOSED Sun + holidays · Wed open</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> 50+ year old neighborhood izakaya. 6-seat counter + 2F tatami. Oden, beef-tendon stew, large-bottle beer.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Yamaneko alt. Japanese-only crowd, 50s/60s regulars. ⚠ Closes 22:00 — hit before Yamaneko if doing both.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区祇園町北側286<br><br><b>↪ ~14 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7762,35.00345,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>我逢人かっぱ (Gahojin Kappa) — late ¥390 everything</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 5 PRIMARY · Tue-Sat 18:00-03:00 · Sun 17:00-00:30 · CLOSED Mon</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> 6-seat counter + 2F tatami. EVERY item ¥390+tax (yakitori, sashimi, tofu, sides). Highball + sake.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Flat-price ¥390 gimmick = no tab math, just stack. Late-night close 03:00 Tue-Sat. The end-of-night pick.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区八坂新地末吉町77<br><br><b>↪ ~15 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7755,35.0021,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>あぶり屋 ぶんぞう (Aburiya Bunzo) — gyutan late</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>STOP 5 SECONDARY · 18:00-03:00 · irregular closing</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Charcoal-grilled skewer counter. Gyutan (beef tongue) + beef cartilage specialty. Sasami, lemon sour, sake.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Late-night alt to Kappa. Gyutan focus = Tohoku influence in Gion. Japanese-majority. Open till 03:00.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区富永町123<br><br><b>↪ ~15 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#major</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.776,35.00295,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
  </Folder>

  <Folder>
    <name>BONUS — discovery zone</name>
    <Placemark>
      <name>🥞 お好み焼 きらく 三条本店 (Okonomiyaki Kiraku Sanjo) — 3rd okonomiyaki</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Wed 11:30-13:40 LO + 17:00-22:00 LO · CLOSED Mondays</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Long-time local-favorite Kyoto okonomiyaki + teppan, casual neighborhood izakaya energy. Hidden-alley feel. Fresh chuhai/lemon sours.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Third okonomiyaki on the map (alongside 3A Mitsuki + 3B Tanto). Locals-heavy. Off the golden path — north-of-Shijo, near Higashiyama station.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区三条通白川橋東4丁目中之町208<br><br><b>↪ ~15 min from Ritz east via Sanjo</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.779,35.00833,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍋 立ち呑み もみじ (Tachinomi Momiji) — sashimi standing</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Daily 12:00-22:00 LO 21:30 · cash only · standing</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Standing counter at Kiyamachi-Shijo gateway. Fresh oden + sashimi small plates + lemon sour + sake.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Off-path Kiyamachi pick. Fresh seafood standing alt if you want sashimi instead of chuhai-bar standing.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区鍋屋町225 萩原ビル 1F<br><br><b>↪ ~13 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7692,35.0041,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍶 SAKE壱 (Sake Ichi) — 200+ sake</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Evening hours · verify on arrival</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Walk-in standing counter, 200+ sake varieties. Simple pairings.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Pure sake-flight pick. Off-path alt to 1A Origami if you want even deeper sake selection.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区材木町<br><br><b>↪ ~12 min from Ritz, near Kawaramachi station</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7695,35.0042,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>たかせ会館 (Takase Kaikan) — Taisho-era kaikan</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Evening · 'sit if empty, stand if crowded'</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> 1920s kaikan housing 10 micro-shops in one converted building. Homemade osozai 5-piece platter, draft beer, sake.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Off-path deepest-locals find. Japanese-only territory.<br><br>Address: Kiyamachi south of Ritz<br><br><b>↪ ~5-7 min south of Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7695,35.0045,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍋 木屋町ゴールデン酒場 (Kiyamachi Golden Sakaba) — Showa late</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Wed 18:00-03:00 · 1F standing · 2F seated</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Showa-retro standing bar. Highball + chuhai + oden + kushiage ¥300-900.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Late-night Kiyamachi anchor (open till 03:00). Off-path but solid backup if 5A/5B aren't right.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区木屋町通六角東側材木町184 都会館ビル 1F<br><br><b>↪ ~12 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76925,35.00854,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>京極スタンド (Kyogoku Stand) — 1927 daytime retro</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Wed 12:00-21:00 LO 20:45 · CLOSED Tuesdays</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> 1927-founded retro working-class dining hall. Large bottle beer, fried oysters, hayashi rice. Multi-generational Japanese crowd.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Daytime/early-evening only — LO 20:45 cuts it off. Off the golden-path (the early-LO rules it out as sequential), but worth a stop if you're walking past before 20:00.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区新京極通四条上ル中之町546<br><br><b>↪ ~14 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76781,35.005,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>立ち呑み ココロノコリ (Kokoronokori) — natural wine</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>~17:00-24:00 · walk-in (¥100/hr seat charge if sitting)</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Natural wine + small plates standing bar near Pontocho south end. Ahi tuna tartare, design-food-industry crowd.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Wine pick (not sake/chuhai). Off-path if you want a wine break.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区下樵木町197<br><br><b>↪ ~13 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.7702,35.004,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>レボリューションブックス (Revolution Books) — bar in bookshop</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>~12:00 to late</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Walk-in standing bar + cookbook shop hybrid, 2F unit. Sashimi, karaage, whiskey.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> The weirdest pick — bar inside a bookshop. Off-path curiosity.<br><br>Address: Kawaramachi area, 2F<br><br><b>↪ ~12 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76945,35.0042,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>🍋 すいば 六角富小路 (Suiba Rokkaku-Tomikoji)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Wed 17:00-23:30 LO 23:30</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Standing chuhai bar. Sawa (lemon sour) + Kyoto sake. ~¥1,500.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> Different Suiba branch from 1B/2B — Rokkaku-Tomikoji branch, west of Teramachi. Off-path option.<br><br>Address: 京都市中京区六角通柳馬場東入ル77 河村ビル1階<br><br><b>↪ ~10 min from Ritz, west of Teramachi</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76651,35.00903,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>山口西店 (Yamaguchi Nishi) — sister of 4B</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>17:30-01:00 · CLOSED Sundays</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Sister of 4B Yamaguchi Daitei Higashi. 8-seat counter + tables + 2F tatami. Beef curry stew, seasoned rice, large beer.<br><br><b>WHY FOR YOU:</b> If 4B is closed/full, same family's other shop. Open till 01:00. Off the golden-path naming because it's redundant with 4B.<br><br>Address: 京都市東山区花見小路末吉町西入ル374-2<br><br><b>↪ ~15 min from Ritz</b>]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#bonus</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.77565,35.0026,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
  </Folder>

  <Folder>
    <name>STATIONS — transit hubs</name>
    <Placemark>
      <name>Kawaramachi (Hankyu line)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Closest to Kiyamachi + Shinkyogoku</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Hankyu Kyoto line. Heart of Kawaramachi-Shijo commercial node.]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#station</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.76879,35.00343,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>Gion-Shijo (Keihan line)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Gion area transit</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Keihan line. All Gion picks within 5-10 min walk.]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#station</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.77272,35.00343,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>

    <Placemark>
      <name>Sanjo (Keihan + Tozai)</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Cross-river hub</b><br><br><b>WHAT IT IS:</b> Sanjo-Ohashi bridge — main Kamogawa crossing.]]></description>
      <styleUrl>#station</styleUrl>
      <Point><coordinates>135.77151,35.0091,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
  </Folder>

</Document>
</kml>
